    "body": "### Problem\n\nThis one's pretty tricky and similar to my previous issue: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/32744\n\nMy best summary of the issue is that when a virtual line is inserted at the same position a concealed line is hidden, the cursor is incorrectly placed on the virtual line.\n\nHopefully the reproducible example will demonstrate this better than the description.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `minimal.lua`:\n\n```lua\nvim.opt.conceallevel = 3\n\nlocal ns = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace('test')\n\nlocal function add_line()\n    vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns, 1, 0, {\n        virt_lines = {\n            { { 'Virtual Line', 'DiffChange' } },\n        },\n        virt_lines_above = false,\n    })\nend\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('BufWinEnter', {\n    callback = function()\n        -- This conceals `Line 3`\n        vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns, 2, 0, {\n            conceal_lines = '',\n        })\n    end,\n})\n\nlocal first = true\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('CursorMoved', {\n    callback = function()\n        -- When we enter `Line 4` for the first time\n        -- schedule adding a virtual line below `Line 2`\n        -- NOTE: This happens around the same time as `Line 3` is concealed\n        local line = vim.api.nvim_win_get_cursor(0)[1]\n        if line == 4 and first then\n            first = false\n            vim.schedule(add_line)\n        end\n    end,\n})\n```\n\n2. `test.txt`:\n\n```text\nLine 1\nLine 2\nLine 3\nLine 4\nLine 5\n```\n\n3. `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua test.txt`\n\n4. Scroll down to the 4th line by pressing `j` 3 times or run `3j`\n \n5. Observe that the cursor is displayed at the start of the virtual line instead of `Line 4`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nFollowing the steps to reproduce the issue:\n\n| Expected Display | Actual Display |\n| ----------------- | -------------- |\n| <img width=\"178\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f021cf08-16a4-499d-a007-1d28ad56100c\" /> | <img width=\"178\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/fc65d577-c7d4-417b-8ec8-4b21df4461cb\" /> |\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-1917+g7371abf755\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno: related to extmarks\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.3.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWezTerm 20240203-110809-5046fc22\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
